se (3) specifically holds the transaction even though only the risk model flagged it.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.1,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The combined output includes both the numeric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The combined output is a data composition function: it must collect results from two models and combine them into a single response structure. This can be tested at Unit level by providing mocked model outputs and verifying the response includes both fields with correct values. Mocking cannot hide a failure here because the test directly inspects the output JSON/object for the presence and correctness of both fields. Real failures (missing risk_score field, missing fraud_probability field, null values, field name typos causing serialization issues) are caught by asserting on the exact output structure and content.","test_description":"Mock the scoring model to return a risk_score=0.75 and the risk model to return fraud_probability=0.60. Call combine_outputs(scoring_result, risk_result) and verify the returned data structure contains both fields with exact values: {'risk_score': 0.75, 'fraud_probability': 0.60}. Verify field names match the reviewer schema exactly (to catch JSON serialization bugs). Test that both fields are present even when only one model flags the transaction (e.g., risk_score=0.2, fraud_probability=0.95 when scoring doesn't flag but risk does).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13405,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13405},"output_tokens"